<item>
    <title>Maruja - Pain To Power</title>
    <link>http://usefulalgorithm.github.io/posts/2026-05-13-paintopower-maruja.html</link>
    <description><![CDATA[<article>
    <section class="header">
        Posted on May 13, 2026
        
        <br>
        
        Tags: <a title="All pages tagged &#39;2025&#39;." href="/tags/2025.html" rel="tag">2025</a>, <a title="All pages tagged &#39;music&#39;." href="/tags/music.html" rel="tag">music</a>
        
    </section>
    <section>
        <p><img src="https://i.discogs.com/VMagyhORA824-WRAvZDxOEmHHLMuNFxTICxPok2yaSQ/rs:fit/g:sm/q:90/h:577/w:599/czM6Ly9kaXNjb2dz/LWRhdGFiYXNlLWlt/YWdlcy9SLTM1MDgw/NjI1LTE3NTc2OTMw/NDktNDY5MC5qcGVn.jpeg" /></p>
<p>看一堆人都把這張歸做後搖，但我覺得唯一稱得上是一般意義上的後搖歌，可能只有最後一首歌？我比較喜歡 “Look Down On Us”、“Trenches” 這些做得很滿、很炸的歌，但除了主唱兼吉他手近乎嘶吼的饒舌跟情緒很滿的薩克斯風旋律之外，我覺得節奏組有點半被主奏樂器蓋著，但細細聽去可以聽到能夠完美撐起歌曲中空隙的貝斯破音跟默默也是一直放招的鼓（可以聽 “Born To Die”），這些地方就還蠻讚的。不過老實說整張聽下來會有一點燥…</p>
<hr />
<p>Fav tracks: Look Down On Us, Born To Die, Trenches</p>
<p>Score: 7.0/10</p>
<p>Release date: 2025-09-12</p>
<p>Labels: Music For Nations</p>
    </section>
</article>
]]></description>
    <pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 00:00:00 UT</pubDate>
    <guid>http://usefulalgorithm.github.io/posts/2026-05-13-paintopower-maruja.html</guid>
    <dc:creator>Tsung-Ju Lii</dc:creator>
</item>
